         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 9/9/73 ¶  ¶ I am anxious to ask you, venerable Sir, whether Streinz' nomenclator fungorum ¶  can generally be relied on. I have this work since some years, and as gradually I have to do so...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.09.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Miles Berkeley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Natural History Museum, London, Botany Library, Berkeley correspondence, vol. 9.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9/9/73</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am anxious to ask you, venerable Sir, whether Streinz' nomenclator fungorum<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="">Streinz (1862).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> can generally be relied on. I have this work since some years, and as gradually I have to do something by my own researches on Fungi for the cryptogamic volumes of the Australian Flora,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78). No cryptogamic volumes were produced.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I am anxious to have your opinion on this opus, as it facilitates reference.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust you will kindly spare a few moments of your precious time to shed light by your unrivalled experience on the little <name key="Clavaria">Clavaria</name> (or whatever it may be) which devastates latterly our <name key="Lolium">Lolium</name> fields.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>How nobly you stood with others to Hooker in his struggles!!<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See MacLeod (1974).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I have no such friend here, but Mr Darwin might induce his neighbour, Mr Edw. Wilson, to stop the mad persecution of his papers here against me, &amp; therewith my ruin!</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With deep regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">If providence spares me life &amp; health, I will devote a year to the study of fungi here in the field, when the phanerogamic portion of the Flora is ready. As yet I could not afford to purchase the necessary works for such studies, my means being absorbed in getting the needful works for the current volumes. The Government funds me no books.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Clavaria">Clavaria</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lolium">Lolium</name>
            </p>
